QObject_iswindowtype

Returns true if the QObject is a window.

Syntax

R = QObject_iswindowtype(h)

Input argument

h

an QObject handle.

Output argument

R

a logical.

Description

Returns true if the QObject is a window; otherwise returns false.

See also

QObject_set (set).

Example

h = errordlg()
r = QObject_iswindowtype(h)

History

Version Description
1.0.0 initial version

Author

Allan CORNET
